      REFACTORED: Originally implemented as Azure Function, then refactored
      to in-process PDF generation (ADR-001 compliant) because:
      - QuestPDF is lightweight (no Chromium dependency)
      - No Azure Function resource was deployed
      - Simpler architecture, fewer moving parts
      - Same ~50ms generation time

      Final Implementation - In-Process PDF Generation:

      1. PDF Document Generation (AnalysisPdfDocument.cs):
         - Location: src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Export/
         - QuestPDF 2025.12.1 (Community license)
         - A4 page size with professional styling
         - Title section with branding color (#0078D4)
         - Metadata bar with generation date, author, analysis ID
         - Executive Summary section with shaded background
         - Main content with paragraph parsing and HTML stripping
         - Entities table (Organizations, People, Dates, Amounts, References)
         - Clauses table with risk level color coding (High/Medium/Low)
         - Page footer with page numbers

      2. PdfExportService.cs:
         - IExportService implementation for ExportFormat.Pdf
         - Direct QuestPDF generation (no HTTP calls)
         - Simple configuration: EnablePdfExport flag only
         - Automatic filename generation with sanitization

      3. Configuration (AnalysisOptions.cs):
         - EnablePdfExport - Feature flag (default: true)
         - Removed: PdfFunctionEndpoint, PdfFunctionKey, PdfGenerationTimeoutSeconds

      4. Unit Tests (15 tests):
         - Format property tests
         - Validation tests (content, title, enabled)
         - ExportAsync tests (success, PDF magic bytes, entities, clauses)
         - Filename sanitization and truncation tests

